author: wsjcom
title: ‘A Quiet Place’ Sneaks Back to Top of Box Office
text:
LOS ANGELES—It was another weekend of buzz versus pure star power at the box office as the word-of-mouth sensation “A Quiet Place” found itself neck-and-neck again with Dwayne Johnson’s “Rampage.” This time buzz had the slight advantage.
Studio estimates on Sunday placed “A Quiet Place,” with $22 million, in first, and “Rampage” in second with $21 million, but it was possible those numbers would shift when final results were tallied Monday.
